news.title: Ulhasnagar civic body launches amnesty scheme for property tax defaulters
news.para: The scheme was implemented on 24th February and will continue until 18th March. This initiative will help the civic body effectively recover arrears of property tax within the UMC jurisdiction, said a UMC official.

news.title: US-based CoStar prepares $1.7 billion bid for Australia's Domain: Source
news.para: CoStar declined to comment. Domain, which is about 60% owned by Australian media group Nine Entertainment, did not immediately respond to a request for comment from Reuters.

news.title: Sebi proposes framework for fast track follow-on offer by REITs, InvITs
news.para: The Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) has sought public comments by March 13 on the proposals.

news.title: Singapore Land & China Jinmao Holdings' joint venture to develop residential project in Shanghai
news.para: The parties won the bid from the Shanghai Municipal Bureau of Planning and Natural Resources for a tender price of 8.96 billion yuan

news.title: Nexus Select Trust acquires MBD Neopolis in Ludhiana for Rs 4,900 million
news.para: The mall comprises aggregate leasable area admeasuring approximately 255,666 sq ft and includes the Radisson Blu Hotel MBD situated at Ferozpur Road.

news.title: BPTP to invest Rs 3,000 crore to develop residential project in Gurugram
news.para: Spread across 12.05 acres, the project has a potential topline of Rs 6,500 crore. It will offer 2BHK and 3BHK residences.

news.title: Google inaugurates its largest office in Bengaluru
news.para: "Located in Bengaluru, one of the world's fastest-growing tech hubs, Ananta is one of our most ambitious ground-up developments.

news.title: KFC relocates its corporate office to Texas
news.para: The relocation of KFC's corporate office from Louisville brought a quick response from political leaders in Kentucky.

news.title: Capping residential rents has choked the supply of properties in Ireland: Eddie Byrne
news.para: Eddie Byrne, CEO of Irish Residential Properties REIT (IRES) , which owns about 4,000 homes in Dublin and Cork, welcomed the government's efforts for reforms that could boost the supply of rental properties while also protecting renters.

news.title: Puducherry government launches pilot project to use drones to survey land
news.para: A team of officials from the survey and revenue departments and municipal administration will undertake aerial drone surveys and publish geo-referenced field maps, integrating the land record data with property-related data.

news.title: Office stock in Chennai to cross 100 million sq ft by 2026-end: Report
news.para: The influx of capital and the entry of prominent developers have facilitated the construction of high-quality office buildings. The private equity investments in Chennai’s office assets touched $1.19 billion in the last two years.

news.title: CCI Group invests Rs 640 crore in a logistics park in Polivakkam, Chennai
news.para: With this latest investment, CCI Group has now allocated a total of Rs 890 crore towards the Polivakkam logistics hub.

news.title: Single-family housing in US drops 8.4% in January 2025
news.para: Single-family housing starts, which account for the bulk of homebuilding, dropped 8.4% to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 993,000 units last month, the Commerce Department's Census Bureau said on Wednesday.

news.title: Uttarakhand's cabinet approves stringent land law
news.para: Chief Minister Pushkar Singh Dhami had first expressed his intentions to bring a stringent land law in the state in September last year.

news.title: Surat civic body to introduce QR code-based identification for properties
news.para: This project aims to provide a digital identity to each property and eventually integrate all municipal services through QR-based identification.

news.title: Real estate sector among top targets for cyber attacks
news.para: "The manufacturing and professional, scientific and technical services sectors account for 19.15% and 15.6% of cyber attacks, respectively, while the construction and real estate sector accounts for 7%," said Pradhasaradhi Chintalapati, a cyber security expert at Arete Incident Response, a cyber threat management company.

news.title: E-khata campaign launched in ULBs: Dharwad deputy commissioner
news.para: On Wednesday, she said citizens who need to make corrections in their property records can submit the required documents to their respective ULBs.

news.title: Rajasthan government allocates Rs 12,000 crore for Jaipur metro line-II
news.para: Finance minister Diya Kumari announced that the project will be executed by the newly formed Rajasthan Metro Railway Corporation (RMRC), a joint venture between the Centre and the state.
